SDO_1: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - Some groups of people must be kept in their place.
SDO_2: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - It’s probably a good thing that certain groups are at the top and other groups are at the bottom.
SDO_3: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - An ideal society requires some groups to be on top and others to be on the bottom.
SDO_4: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - Some groups of people are simply inferior to other groups.
SDO_5: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - Groups at the bottom are just as deserving as groups at the top.
SDO_6: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - No one group should dominate in society.
SDO_7: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - Groups at the bottom should not have to stay in their place.
SDO_8: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - Group dominance is a poor principle.
SDO_9: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - We should not push for group equality.
SDO_10: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - We shouldn’t try to guarantee that every group has the same quality of life.
SDO_11: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - It is unjust to try to make groups equal.
SDO_12: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - Group equality should not be our primary goal.
SDO_13: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - We should work to give all groups an equal chance to succeed.
SDO_14: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - We should do what we can to equalize conditions for different groups.
SDO_15: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - No matter how much effort it takes, we ought to strive to ensure that all groups have the same chance in life.
SDO_16: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - Group equality should be our ideal.

RFS_1: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - God has given humanity a complete, unfailing guide to happiness and salvation, which must be totally followed.
RFS_2: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - No single book of religious teachings contains all the intrinsic, fundamental truths about life.
RFS_3: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - The basic cause of evil in this world is Satan, who is still constantly and ferociously fighting against God.
RFS_4: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - It is more important to be a good person than to believe in God and the right religion.
RFS_5: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - There is a particular set of religious teachings in this world that are so true, you can’t go any “deeper” because they are the basic, bedrock message that God has given humanity.
RFS_6: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - When you get right down to it, there are basically only two kinds of people in the world: the Righteous, who will be rewarded by God; and the rest, who will not.
RFS_7: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - Scriptures may contain general truths, but they should NOT be considered completely, literally true from beginning to end.
RFS_8: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - To lead the best, most meaningful life, one must belong to the one, fundamentally true religion.
RFS_9: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - “Satan” is just the name people give to their own bad impulses. There really is no such thing as a diabolical “Prince of Darkness” who tempts us.
RFS_10: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - Whenever science and sacred scripture conflict, science is probably right.
RFS_11: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - The fundamentals of God’s religion should never be tampered with or compromised with others’ beliefs.
RFS_12: Please indicate your level of agreement (or disagreement) with each of the following statements. - All of the religions in the world have flaws and wrong teachings. There is no perfectly true, right religion.
